## What I built

A fully runnable Flask voting platform in `C:\Users\Darko\AppData\Local\Temp\csj_gen_4mtga53h`:

```
app.py                      # routes + SQLite schema (one file)
requirements.txt            # Flask 3 + Werkzeug
README.md                   # run instructions (port 5081)
.gitignore
templates/
  base.html  index.html  election_detail.html
  login.html  register.html  new_election.html
```

## How it meets the requirements

- **Admin creates elections** — `/admin/elections/new` (admin-only) takes a title, description, candidates (one per line), and open/close times. Validates ≥2 candidates and close-after-open.
- **Registered users vote once** — `/register` + `/login` with hashed passwords (Werkzeug). The "exactly one vote per election" rule is enforced at the DB level by `UNIQUE(election_id, user_id)` on the `votes` table, not just in app logic — so it's race-safe.
- **Results after close** — an election is `upcoming` / `open` / `closed` based on current time vs. its window. Vote tallies are only queried and rendered once `status == "closed"`; before that the page only shows the ballot or a "you've voted" confirmation.
- **SQLite** — single `voting.db` file, created and seeded automatically on first run.

A bootstrap admin (`admin` / `admin123`) is seeded on first launch so you can create an election immediately; both are overridable via `ADMIN_USERNAME` / `ADMIN_PASSWORD` env vars.

