## Core behavior
- **Admin** creates elections with a title, description, ≥2 candidates (one per line), and UTC open/close times.
- **Registered users** see an election as *upcoming / open / closed*; can vote exactly once while open.
- **Results** are revealed only after `close_at` passes (enforced server-side on both the detail and `/results` routes).
- Admin is bootstrapped from `ADMIN_USERNAME`/`ADMIN_PASSWORD` env vars on first run.

## Security mapping (OWASP)
- **SQL injection** — every query uses `?` placeholders; no string-built SQL.
- **Passwords** — Argon2id (salted) via `argon2-cffi`; session reset on login (anti-fixation); rehash-on-login; timing-equalized verify for unknown users.
- **XSS** — Jinja2 auto-escaping, allow-list input validation, and a strict CSP (`script-src 'self'`, `frame-ancestors 'none'`, `base-uri 'none'`).
- **CSRF** — Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` on every POST (login, register, vote, create, logout).
- **Access control / IDOR** — voter `user_id` comes from the session (never the form), candidate-belongs-to-election is verified, admin routes guarded, `next` open-redirect blocked.
- **Double-vote** — app check **plus** `UNIQUE(election_id, user_id)` for race safety.
- **Cookies** — `HttpOnly` + `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` on in production (off in dev so local HTTP works), HSTS when secure.
- **Headers** — X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy.
- **Secrets** — `SECRET_KEY` from env (required in production); nothing hardcoded.
- **Errors** — generic 400/403/404/500 pages; stack traces logged server-side only.

