## What I built

A complete Express file-storage app — **File Vault** — at `C:\Users\Darko\AppData\Local\Temp\csj_gen_psptrn59`:

```
package.json          deps + start script (port 5082)
README.md             setup / usage / security notes
.gitignore
src/
  app.js              Express setup, sessions, flash, route mounting, error handler
  db.js               better-sqlite3 connection + schema (users / files / shares)
  storage.js          per-user upload folders, multer config, path-traversal guard
  auth.js             session user loading + requireAuth
  routes/
    accounts.js       register / login / logout (bcrypt, session regen on login)
    files.js          upload / list / download / delete — owner-scoped
    shares.js         create / list / revoke + public /s/:token read access
views/*.ejs           server-rendered UI
public/style.css
data/  uploads/        created at runtime (gitignored)
```

## How it meets the requirements

- **Personal folders** — uploads land in `uploads/<userId>/` with random on-disk names; the original filename is kept in the DB.
- **Share links → read access to one file** — `POST /files/:id/shares` mints a 24-byte random `base64url` token; `GET /s/:token` (and `/download`) serve that single file publicly, no login.
- **Manage & revoke** — `/shares` lists a user's links; `POST /shares/:id/revoke` flips `revoked=1`, immediately breaking the link.
- **DB + disk split** — SQLite (`data/app.db`) for users/files/shares metadata; file bytes on disk.
- **Security** — bcrypt password hashing, HTTP-only session cookies with session regeneration on login, ownership checks on every file/share action, path-traversal guard in `storedFilePath`, cascade deletes.

